Monday.com provides two types of MCP servers to integrate AI agents with its platform [1]. The Platform MCP allows agents to read and write work data such as boards, items, and users [1]. The Apps MCP is a specialized server used by developers to manage, scaffold, and deploy applications within the monday apps framework [1].

You can connect using the hosted MCP service for a managed experience with no local setup [1][2], or use the @mondaydotcomorg/monday-api-mcp package to run the server locally [3][4].

To configure the local server in your MCP settings:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "monday-api-mcp": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@mondaydotcomorg/monday-api-mcp@latest"],
      "env": {
        "MONDAY_TOKEN": "your_api_token"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

When using the local server, you can toggle between Platform and Apps functionality by passing the --mode flag, such as --mode apps [1][3]. Note that hosted tool calls count toward your account's daily API limits [1].
